# ðŸ”§ **Most Used Real-Time Linux Troubleshooting & Daily Commands**

## **1. System Check**

```
top            # CPU/Memory live usage
free -h        # Memory usage
df -h          # Disk usage
uptime         # Server load & uptime
```

## **2. Process Troubleshooting**

```
ps aux                     # List processes
ps aux | grep <name>       # Search process
kill -9 <PID>              # Kill process
```

## **3. Network Troubleshooting**

```
ping google.com            # Connectivity
curl -I http://site.com    # Check website response
ip a                       # Show IP
ss -tulnp                  # Ports running
```

## **4. Log Check**

```
tail -f /var/log/syslog
tail -f /var/log/messages
journalctl -xe
```

## **5. File & Directory**

```
ls                         # List files
cd folder/                 # Move
pwd                        # Current path
touch file.txt             # Create file
rm file.txt                # Delete file
mkdir dir                  # Create folder
rm -r dir                  # Delete folder
```

## **6. Copy / Move**

```
cp file1 file2
mv file1 folder/
```

## **7. Permissions**

```
chmod 755 file.sh
chown user:group file
```

## **8. View & Edit Files**

```
cat file.txt
less file.txt
nano file.txt
```

## **9. Service Management**

```
systemctl start nginx
systemctl stop nginx
systemctl restart nginx
systemctl status nginx
```

## **10. Package Install**

```
sudo apt install <pkg>     # Ubuntu/Debian
sudo yum install <pkg>     # RHEL/CentOS
```

## **11. Users**

```
useradd testuser
passwd testuser
id testuser
```

